WEBVTT

00:02.383 --> 00:06.234
It's 10:27 and President
Dalton is still trailing.

00:06.235 --> 00:08.333
Now, were you expecting
it to be this close?

00:08.334 --> 00:11.463
- No one was...
- Santa Fe results are coming in fast.

00:11.490 --> 00:13.392
Projections still have him
down by three points.

00:13.393 --> 00:14.526
Well, forget the projection.

00:14.527 --> 00:16.261
Our ground game was better in Santa Fe.

00:16.262 --> 00:17.663
We can still close this gap.

00:17.664 --> 00:19.631
I think it's safe to say
the Dalton campaign

00:19.632 --> 00:20.833
took New Mexico for granted.

00:20.834 --> 00:22.468
- He had a ground operation
- (various phones ringing)

00:22.469 --> 00:24.503
twice the size of Evans, didn't matter.

00:24.504 --> 00:26.727
Ladies and gentlemen, we are
ready to make a projection.

00:26.728 --> 00:28.574
- DALTON: What?
- This is wrong.

00:28.575 --> 00:30.309
New Mexico will not go to Dalton.

00:30.310 --> 00:33.378
That makes it official,
he has lost the race.

00:33.379 --> 00:36.582
President Conrad Dalton
will be a one-term president.

00:36.583 --> 00:39.251
Can't make a projection
when-when it's this tight.

00:39.252 --> 00:41.653
20% of the vote is still uncounted.

00:41.654 --> 00:43.055
AP just made the same call.

00:43.056 --> 00:45.524
- (phone beeping)
- What the hell happened to margin of error?

00:45.525 --> 00:47.658
It's over, Russell.

00:51.663 --> 00:55.033
If it's all the same to everyone,

00:55.034 --> 00:57.402
I'd prefer to do the
postmortem tomorrow.

00:57.403 --> 01:00.638
It was a good fight.

